SAY NAME1 ~Firebomb~
SAY NAME2 ~Charcoal Smoke Grenade~
SAY DESC ~This seemingly innocuous metal object is in fact a cunning weapon created by Phalh. When the fuse is lit and the grenade thrown, the resulting explosion leaves a burning-hot cloud of black smoke that causes the throat to dry and the eyes to water, making it a deadly tool for incapacitation.

STATISTICS:

Special: When thrown, a cloud of burning smoke erupts in the targeted location, dealing 1d3 fire damage per round and blinding all targets and inflcting 75% spell failure. A Saving Throw vs. Breath Weapons at -2 may be made to avoid the effect. If the user enters the smoke, they gain the benefits of Improved Invisibility for 1 round instead. The effects persist for up to 3 rounds after leaving the cloud.
Duration: 3 rounds

Weight: 1~
